-- South Africa Aiming to Remove Structural Growth Restraints, Minister Says
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2010-09-22T06:20:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/south-africa-aiming-to-remove-structural-growth-restraints-minister-says.html
South African Economic Development
Minister Ebrahim Patel said growth in Africa’s largest economy
is being restrained by structural issues, such as a shortage of
skills and lack of competition.  The country’s “new growth path” aims to address
impediments to its expansion, Patel told business people at a
function before the start of the third day of the ruling African
National Congress’ National General Council today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
